Changes — message-router.ts handlePluginUpdate:
The current (post-US-005) handler reads validated → toPluginMeta → storePluginsBatch → upsertPreScript → injectPluginIntoMatchingTabs. Reorder + add hash compare:
```ts
const previous = await getPluginMeta(validated.name);
const meta = toPluginMeta(validated);

await storePluginsBatch([meta]);
await upsertPreScript(meta);

const hashChanged =
  meta.preScriptFile !== undefined &&
  previous?.preScriptFile !== undefined &&
  previous.preScriptHash !== meta.preScriptHash;

if (hashChanged) {
  // Pre-script content changed for an already-registered plugin. Chrome's
  // registered scripts only fire on FUTURE navigations, so tabs currently
  // open with the stale pre-script must be reloaded for the new pre-script
  // to take effect. First-time registrations (previous.preScriptFile was
  // undefined) are NOT auto-reloaded — forcing a reload on first install
  // would surprise the user mid-task; the new registration applies on the
  // user's next navigation.
  const matchingTabIds = await queryMatchingTabIds(meta.urlPatterns, meta.excludePatterns);
  for (const tabId of matchingTabIds) {
    try {
      await chrome.tabs.reload(tabId);
    } catch (e) {
      console.warn(`[opentabs] failed to reload tab ${tabId} after pre-script hash change:`, e);
    }
  }
}

// Existing: forced re-injection so the new IIFE overwrites the stale adapter
```
Add `import { getPluginMeta } from './plugin-storage.js';` if not already imported (the existing file already imports getAllPluginMeta and storePluginsBatch — same module).
Add `import { queryMatchingTabIds } from './iife-injection.js';` alongside the existing `injectPluginIntoMatchingTabs, cleanupAdaptersInMatchingTabs` import (same module).

Constraints:
- Do NOT attempt to persist our own registration cache in chrome.storage. chrome.scripting.getRegisteredContentScripts IS the source of truth inside the extension context; syncPreScripts already reconciles.
- Do NOT auto-reload tabs on first-time registration (previous.preScriptFile === undefined). That would break the user's in-progress session whenever a new plugin gets installed. The installation path shows up in the side panel; the user decides when to reload.
- Do NOT auto-reload on plugin.uninstall either — removePreScript unregisters the script, but leaving the current page state intact is less disruptive than a forced reload.
- The service-worker wake-up path (top-level reinject chain) runs frequently; keep it cheap. getAllPluginMeta hits the in-memory cache first (invalidatePluginCache is only called on storage change events), so the extra syncPreScripts call is dominated by chrome.scripting.getRegisteredContentScripts latency. Do NOT add any additional work inside this chain.
- `queryMatchingTabIds` already handles exclude patterns — do NOT add a post-filter.

